04530nam a2200673Ia 9781487579340DE-B159720240426104009.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240426t19621962onc    fo  d z      eng d  a97814875793407 a10.3138/97814875793402doi  a(DE-B1597)527999  a(OCoLC)1121052356  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aonccCA-ON 4aHV5303b.A58 7aSEL0060002bisacsh04a616.8612221 aPopham, Robert E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut12aA Decade of Alcoholism Research :bA review of the research activities of the Alcoholism and Drug Addiction Research Foundation of Ontario, 1951–1961 /cWolfgang Schmidt, Robert E. Popham. 1aToronto : bUniversity of Toronto Press, c[1962] 4c©1962  a1 online resource (72 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aHeritage00tFrontmatter -- tFOREWORD -- tCONTENTS -- tI. HISTORY OF THE RESEARCH OPERATION -- tII. THE CHARACTER AND RESULTS OF FOUNDATION RESEARCH -- tIll. RETROSPECT AND PROSPECT -- tCLASSIFIED LIST OF PROJECTS AND RESEARCH REPORTS -- tINDEX OF INVESTIGATORS0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe year 1961 marked the beginning of the second decade of operation of the Alcoholism Research Foundation of Ontario. It also marked the end, in certain respects, of a stage in its development as a research organization. The most concrete event in this regard was an amendment to the act governing the Foundation, which added the words 'Drug Addiction' to its name and broadened its legitimate scope to include the study of virtually all forms of addictive behaviour. The year appeared to mark the end of a formative and largely exploratory stage of research and the beginning of a period characterized by a more precise sense of overall direction. This is best revealed through an examination of the history of the Foundation's research endeavour and of the character and results of the numerous projects which have been conducted under its auspices. Such an examination was attempted in the research section of the 1961 Annual Report of the Foundation. However, because of the special purpose and highly restricted readership for which this report was designed, it seemed desirable to publish the material subsequently in a form suitable for wider distribution. Accordingly, the present volume was prepared, and comprises a somewhat revised and expanded version of the original review. It is hoped that it will prove of value not only to research workers but also to those whose primary responsibilities in the alcoholism field are in the realm of treatment, education, or the administration of programs with these functions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAlcoholismvBibliography. 0aAlcoholismxResearchzOntario. 0aDrug abusexResearchzOntario. 7aSELF-HELP / Substance Abuse & Addictions / Alcohol.2bisacsh1 aSchmidt, Wolfgang, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757934040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487579340423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487579340/original  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles